<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="P" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Pair1" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Pair,</orth> subst. 1) two things of the same kind used together: <emph>a p. of maiden worlds</emph> (i. e. breasts) <bibl n="shak. luc 408" default="NO" valid="yes">Lucr. 408</bibl>. <cit><quote>of eyes,</quote> <bibl n="shak. luc 408" default="NO" valid="yes">Lucr. 408</bibl></cit> <bibl n="shak. jn 4.1.99" default="NO" valid="yes">John IV, 1, 99</bibl>. <cit><quote>of anchoring hooks,</quote> <bibl n="shak. tgv 3.1.118" default="NO" valid="yes">Gent. III, 1, 118</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>of horns,</quote> <bibl n="shak. wiv 5.1.7" default="NO" valid="yes">Wiv. V, 1, 7</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>of shears,</quote> <bibl n="shak. mm 1.2.28" default="NO" valid="yes">Meas. I, 2, 28</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>of stocks,</quote> <bibl n="shak. err 3.1.60" default="NO" valid="yes">Err. III, 1, 60</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. err 3.1.2" default="NO" valid="yes">Shr. Ind. 1, 2.</bibl> <cit><quote>of lips,</quote> <bibl n="shak. ayl 3.4.16" default="NO" valid="yes">As III, 4, 16</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>of stairs,</quote> <bibl n="shak. ayl 5.2.41" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 2, 41</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>of breeches,</quote> <bibl n="shak. shr 3.2.44" default="NO" valid="yes">Shr. III, 2, 44</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>of boots,</quote> <bibl n="shak. shr 3.2.44" default="NO" valid="yes">Shr. III, 2, 44</bibl></cit> <cit><quote>of gloves,</quote> <bibl n="shak. wt 4.4.253" default="NO" valid="yes">Wint. IV, 4, 253</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>of gallows,</quote> <bibl n="shak. 1h4 2.1.74" default="NO" valid="yes">H4A II, 1, 74</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>of heels,</quote> <bibl n="shak. 1h4 2.4.53" default="NO" valid="yes">II, 4, 53</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>of sheets,</quote> <bibl n="shak. 2h4 2.4.243" default="NO" valid="yes">H4B II, 4, 243</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>of legs,</quote> <bibl n="shak. h5 3.6.158" default="NO" valid="yes">H5 III, 6, 158</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>of spectacles,</quote> <bibl n="shak. tro 4.4.14" default="NO" valid="yes">Troil. IV, 4, 14</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>of chaps,</quote> <bibl n="shak. ant 3.5.14" default="NO" valid="yes">Ant. III, 5, 14</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>of bases,</quote> <bibl n="shak. per 2.1.167" default="NO" valid="yes">Per. II, 1, 167</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. per 2.1.167" default="NO" valid="yes">Per. II, 1, 167</bibl> Uninflected in the plural: <cit><quote>twenty p. of eyes,</quote> <bibl n="shak. tgv 2.4.95" default="NO" valid="yes">Gent. II, 4, 95</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>how many p. of stockings,</quote> <bibl n="shak. 2h4 2.2.17" default="NO" valid="yes">H4B II, 2, 17</bibl></cit>.<lb />2) couple, brace: <cit><quote>a p. of honourable men,</quote> <bibl n="shak. ado 5.1.275" default="NO" valid="yes">Ado V, 1, 275</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>a p. of these,</quote> <bibl n="shak. tn 3.1.55" default="NO" valid="yes">Tw. III, 1, 55</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>of kings,</quote> <bibl n="shak. wt 5.3.146" default="NO" valid="yes">Wint. V, 3, 146</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>of carved saints,</quote> <bibl n="shak. r2 3.3.152" default="NO" valid="yes">R2 III, 3, 152</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>of graves,</quote> <bibl n="shak. r2 3.3.152" default="NO" valid="yes">R2 III, 3, 152</bibl></cit> <cit><quote>of knaves,</quote> <bibl n="shak. 2h6 1.2.103" default="NO" valid="yes">H6B I, 2, 103</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>of bleeding hearts,</quote> <bibl n="shak. r3 4.4.272" default="NO" valid="yes">R3 IV, 4, 272</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>of strange ones,</quote> <bibl n="shak. cor 2.1.89" default="NO" valid="yes">Cor. II, 1, 89</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>of tribunes,</quote> <bibl n="shak. cor 5.1.16" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 1, 16</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>of hell-hounds,</quote> <bibl n="shak. tit 5.2.144" default="NO" valid="yes">Tit. V, 2, 144</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>of maidenhoods,</quote> <bibl n="shak. rom 3.2.13" default="NO" valid="yes">Rom. III, 2, 13</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>of kisses,</quote> <bibl n="shak. ham 3.4.184" default="NO" valid="yes">Hml. III, 4, 184</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>of indentures,</quote> <bibl n="shak. ham 5.1.119" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 1, 119</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>of twins,</quote> <bibl n="shak. ant 3.10.12" default="NO" valid="yes">Ant. III, 10, 12</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>of sons,</quote> <bibl n="shak. cym 5.5.356" default="NO" valid="yes">Cymb. V, 5, 356</bibl></cit>. == two beings of different sex joined in love: <bibl n="shak. ayl 5.4.37" default="NO" valid="yes">As V, 4, 37</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h6 2.2.30" default="NO" valid="yes">H6A II, 2, 30</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h6 2.2.30" default="NO" valid="yes">H6A II, 2, 30</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ant 1.1.37" default="NO" valid="yes">Ant. I, 1, 37</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ant 5.2.363" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 2, 363</bibl>. Plur. <emph>--s</emph>: <cit><quote>the --s of faithful lovers,</quote> <bibl n="shak. mnd 4.1.96" default="NO" valid="yes">Mids. IV, 1, 96</bibl></cit>.
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>